mdRecord.dcterms:title: "Intelligence of Frogs" and etc; 03 of 03
mdRecord.dcterms:description: 3. Doepner/Faulds--NotesItems 33-74, cloth sleeve"Natural History Notes"; A section of a periodical with multiple topics. "Intelligence of Frogs" mentions works and arguments of Charles C. Abbott and a Mr. Romanes. "Fight Between a Fox and a Sheep" regards a reported incident by P. W. Godsal, taken from the Scotsman. "Effects of the Recent Gales on Birds" discusses nature's effect on sea birds.; Sunlight, p. 174-176; 2 leaves; DF n.a.
